amber /ˈæmbə/

1. N-UNCOUNT Amber is a hard yellowish-brown substance used for making jewellery. 琥珀 [usu N n] 

例： ...an amber choker with matching earrings. …一条琥珀贴颈短项链和相配的耳环。 

2. COLOR Amber is used to describe things that are yellowish-brown in colour. 琥珀色 (的) 

例： A burst of sunshine sent a beam of amber light through the window. 一道阳光透过窗户射进了一束琥珀色的光。 

3. COLOR An amber traffic light is yellow. 黄色 (的) 

例： Cars did not stop when the lights were on amber. 当交通灯是黄色时汽车没有停下来。

